This paper discusses the adaptation of probabilities for Evolutionary Algorithm (EA) search operators, which is a topic related to machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses statistical interpretations and measurements, which are also relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves testing and analyzing data, which falls under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the EA, which is related to the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
